==English==
===Etymology===
Late Latin ''[[elongare]]'', ''[[elongat-]]'', a combination of ''[[ex-]]'' ("[[out]]") + ''[[longus]]'' ("[[long]]")

===Adjective===
'''elongate'''
#[[lengthened]], [[extended]].
#[[slender]].
===Translations===
*Romanian: [[alungit]], [[elongat]], [[lungit]], [[prelung]], [[prelungit]]

===Verb===
'''elongate'''

# Make [[long]] or [[longer]] by [[pull]]ing and [[stretc]]hing; to make [[elongated]].

